And I want to look at
the line that is

00:00:34.650 --> 00:00:36.200
spanned by this vector.

00:00:36.200 --> 00:00:39.340
So let me just define some line
L, and it's equal to the

00:00:39.340 --> 00:00:47.850
set of t times 1, 2, where
t is any real number.

00:00:47.850 --> 00:00:50.930
So this is just a line with
a slope of 2, right?

00:00:50.930 --> 00:00:53.185
You rise 2 for every
1 you go over.

00:00:53.185 --> 00:00:57.270
So let me draw my line
just like this.

00:00:57.270 --> 00:01:00.520
There's nothing new
at this point.

00:01:00.520 --> 00:01:03.220
Let me draw it a little
bit better than that.

00:01:03.220 --> 00:01:04.569
There you go.

00:01:04.569 --> 00:01:06.230
And it keeps going, because
obviously, you could get

00:01:06.230 --> 00:01:09.150
