00:04:40.040 --> 00:04:43.180
And then our second column in A
would be the transformation

00:04:43.180 --> 00:04:45.750
applied to 0, 1.

00:04:45.750 --> 00:04:49.690
And if we were dealing in Rn,
we would do this n times and

00:04:49.690 --> 00:04:51.420
we would have the
n basis vectors.

00:04:51.420 --> 00:04:53.940
We've seen this multiple,
multiple times.

00:04:53.940 --> 00:04:56.290
Now, in the past, when we
were constructing these

00:04:56.290 --> 00:04:59.440
transformation matrices, finding
these things were

00:04:59.440 --> 00:05:02.300
pretty straightforward, but
you'll see now it's not that

00:05:02.300 --> 00:05:03.010
